# Version management & release phases

> **Compliance:** Mandatory (`agents-mandatory.mdc`). Read **before** planning or implementing any change that ships to users, touches `gradle/app-version.properties`, Supabase migrations, or release workflows.

This repo follows **[Semantic Versioning 2.0.0](https://semver.org/)** (`MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`) for user-facing `version.name`, plus optional prerelease segments for beta. Phase (alpha/beta/prod) is determined by **branch + CI track + prerelease** — not by the version string alone.

## Two numbers users and stores care about

| Field | Example | Audience | Rule |
|-------|---------|----------|------|
| **`version.name`** | `1.4.0` | End users, support, release notes | SemVer marketing version — bump only via policy below |
| **`version.code`** | `136` | Play Store / App Store (internal) | **Monotonic integer** — must increase on every store upload; never reused |

**Industry norm (Android / iOS):** users see a simple `X.Y.Z`; stores enforce a separate always-increasing build number. CI further encodes track in `versionCode` via `100_000 + run_number × 3 + trackOffset` (see `ci-cd.mdc`). Do not expose raw CI build codes in consumer UI.

---

## SemVer bump policy (`MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`)

Terminology maps to [semver.org](https://semver.org/):

| Bump | SemVer segment | When to use | Ammò examples |
|------|----------------|-------------|---------------|
| **PATCH** | `Z` in `X.Y.Z` | Backward-compatible **bug fixes**, security patches, performance fixes, copy/i18n corrections, test-only CI changes that ship no user-visible feature | Grocery sync crash, RTL layout fix, typo in onboarding |
| **MINOR** | `Y` in `X.Y.Z` | Backward-compatible **new features** or UX capability; additive API/schema changes with migration | Food emoji thumbnails, new household role UI, AI suggestion chips |
| **MAJOR** | `X` in `X.Y.Z` | **Breaking** changes: incompatible data model, auth/session contract change, removed features, migrations that cannot coexist with prior app versions | Household schema redesign, dropping offline mode, login flow that invalidates existing sessions |

### Agent decision checklist (before recommending a bump)

1. **Would an older app version break** if it kept using the same backend or local data? → **MAJOR**
2. **Is there new user-visible capability** but old clients still work? → **MINOR**
3. **Only fixes / polish / no new capability?** → **PATCH**
4. **Production hotfix on a tagged release?** → **PATCH** on the hotfix line (`v1.3.1-hotfix.1`), not MINOR/MAJOR unless explicitly approved

### What does *not* warrant a MINOR or MAJOR

- Refactors with no user-visible change → ship on alpha; **no version bump** until release
- Dependency bumps (Kotlin, Compose) → PATCH if shipping alone; MINOR if bundled with features
- Firebase YAML / test-only changes → no bump
- Beta iteration → **no** `version.name` change; suffix stays `-beta`

### Tooling

```bash
./scripts/bump-app-version.sh patch|minor|major|none   # none = version.code only
gh workflow run "KMP CI" --ref main -f job=release -f version_bump=patch
```

`version_bump`: `major` | `minor` | `patch` | `none`. All modes except manual property edits clear `version.prerelease`.

