## Version string format (`AppVersionFormatter`)

```kotlin
// Empty prerelease → "1.3.1"; with prerelease → "1.3.1-beta" or "1.3.1-alpha"
formatVersionName(name, prerelease)
```

| `version.prerelease` | Display | `IS_PRERELEASE` |
|----------------------|---------|-----------------|
| *(omitted)* | `1.3.1` | `false` |
| `alpha` | `1.3.1-alpha` | `true` |
| `beta` | `1.3.1-beta` | `true` |
| `rc.1` | `1.3.1-rc.1` | `true` *(supported; not used by CI today)* |

- Source of truth: `gradle/app-version.properties`
- CI stamps `alpha` or `beta` in-memory only — never committed to git.

