## Prerelease suffix contract (non-negotiable)

Every build distributed to any user **must** carry exactly the right suffix. This is enforced in CI and must be preserved on every future change to the workflow, the UI version label, or any tooling that reads `version.prerelease`.

| Track | `version.prerelease` value | In-app display | How it is set |
|-------|---------------------------|---------------|---------------|
| **Alpha** (`main` / Firebase) | `alpha` | `X.Y.Z-alpha` | `distribute-alpha` job stamps in-memory |
| **Beta** (`release/**` / Play Closed) | `beta` | `X.Y.Z-beta` | `distribute-beta` job stamps in-memory |
| **Production** (`v*` tag / Play Production) | *(absent)* | `X.Y.Z` | `bump-app-version.sh` clears on named release |

### Rules for agents and CI changes

1. **Never remove or skip the stamp step** in `distribute-alpha` or `distribute-beta` — the step that writes `version.prerelease=alpha|beta` to `gradle/app-version.properties` before the build is the only mechanism that produces the correct suffix.
2. **Never commit `version.prerelease`** — stamps are build-time only (in-memory `sed`/`echo`). The file on `main` and `release/*` must not contain a `version.prerelease` key.
3. **Never change the suffix values** (`alpha`, `beta`) without updating this table, the CI stamp steps, and re-running both Gradle gates.
4. **UI always uses `home_app_version` (`"Version %1$s"`)** — `AppBuildInfo.VERSION_NAME` already contains the suffix; do not add a separate IS_PRERELEASE branch or a new string key for channel labelling.
5. **Production builds must have no suffix** — if `version.prerelease` is present in the properties file when a production tag fires, it is a release blocker.

### Self-review gate (add to PR checklist when touching CI or version tooling)

- [ ] `distribute-alpha` still stamps `version.prerelease=alpha` before `assembleDebug`
- [ ] `distribute-beta` still stamps `version.prerelease=beta` before the signed AAB build
- [ ] `gradle/app-version.properties` on `main` has **no** `version.prerelease` key
- [ ] `home_app_version` string key exists in all 8 locale files with a `%1$s` placeholder

