## Phase-specific agent behaviour

### Alpha (`main` integration)

**Goal:** Rapid iteration. **No `version.name` bump** per merge.

- New features, refactors, schema changes allowed.
- Breaking changes OK with migrations + tests.
- Auto `distribute-alpha` on green `main` push.
- CI stamps `version.prerelease=alpha` in-memory (not committed); app shows `X.Y.Z-alpha`.
- `version.name` evolves per SemVer when a named `release` job is dispatched (PATCH for fixes, MINOR for features, MAJOR for breaking changes).

### Beta (`release/X.Y` stabilisation)

**Goal:** Stabilisation — **feature freeze**.

- **Reject new features** unless user explicitly overrides.
- PATCH-level fixes only; no MINOR/MAJOR bump on the branch.
- CI stamps `version.prerelease=beta` in-memory (not committed); app shows `X.Y.Z-beta`.
- Strict self-review per `review-commit.mdc`.

### Production (tagged release / hotfix)

**Goal:** Minimal blast radius.

- **Hotfixes only** — PATCH bump.
- **No breaking changes.**
- Block destructive DB ops without explicit human override.
- Update `distribution/whatsnew/whatsnew-en-US` before `v*` tag.
- Tag: `git tag vX.Y.Z && git push origin vX.Y.Z`
- Hotfix: `git tag vX.Y.Z-hotfix.N main && git push origin vX.Y.Z-hotfix.N`

